    "long_instructions": "# Debugging with Mike and Katie\r\n\r\nMike was absent on the day we learned loops, so he's still been making songs the long way with lots of blocks. Katie is trying to help him convert his code into loops, but there's a bug somewhere. Let's debug Katie's code to help her and Mike!\r\n\r\nMike's code is still in the workplace as _ghost blocks_ - you can't interact with them, but you can still preview what the song sounds like! Katie's blocks with loops are off to the side for now\r\n\r\n## Do This\r\n\r\n1) Press the run button to hear Mike's original song\r\n2) Drag Katie's blocks underneath `when run`. Once you let go, Mike's blocks will disappear and the timeline will update!\r\n\r\n::: details [**Click to see how this works!**]\r\n![](https://images.code.org/39289b53e8b56976605b27e6d2244cd8-image-1741117805411.gif)\r\n:::\r\n\r\n3) The new timeline doesn't match with Mike's song. Can you rearrange the blocks so it matches Mike's original song?\r\n    - You can remove Katie's blocks from underneath `when run` to see Mike's blocks again! This can help you compare and make sure you're on the right track!",
